  "commentary": "With SPX at 7106.88 sitting just below the GEX flip at 7111 in a PIN regime, dealers are currently net short gamma and will likely amplify any moves - buying if we push higher through 7111-7115 or selling if we break below 7100. The massive negative gamma wall at 7110 (-9.87B) creates significant instability right at current levels, while the positive gamma wall at 7200 (+7.58B) acts as a strong resistance magnet above. Key levels to watch are the 7111 flip point for regime change and the 7100 support level - a break below likely triggers accelerated selling into the 7000s.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile whipsaw action with a bias toward the 7200 magnet, but watch for potential downside acceleration if 7100 breaks.",
